parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the DRL can reduce the vehicle's visibility to other drivers, especially during twilight or inclement weather, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: DRLs do not turn on
DRLs are partially lit
DRLs are dim
DRLs burn out prematurely
DRLs fail to operate on one or both sides of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The peeling of paint can lead to rust and corrosion, compromising the vehicle's structure and safety.
symptoms: Paint peeling off
especially above the back window.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loud static and beeping noises from the audio unit can be distracting and potentially damaging to the ears of the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Loud static and beeping noises from the audio unit
even when the system is turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the backup camera can lead to accidents or injuries, especially when reversing.
symptoms: The backup camera screen is black
or the image is distorted
with grid lines still visible.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without the foot being on the accelerator
and braking does not stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
often without warning
and may not restart immediately.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the VSA solenoid can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: All ABS
steering
traction
and brake lights are on in the car
indicating a VSA solenoid malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can lead to discomfort and heat-related illnesses, especially in hot climates.
symptoms: The air conditioning system stops working
making it difficult to drive in hot weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trunk light activation switch can lead to safety and visibility issues, especially when retrieving or placing items in the trunk at night.
symptoms: The trunk light does not turn on when the trunk is opened
making it difficult to see in the dark.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rattling noise from the doors can be distracting and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Rattling noise from the driver-side door when driving over 70 mph
and from the passenger-side door when going over small bumps and dips in the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A vehicle fire can lead to injuries, fatalities, or property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle catches on fire without warning
often while driving on the freeway.
